<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871007-0129 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:ERC International Inc.</HL><DD> 10/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ERCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   ERC International Inc. said it signed an agreement to purchase W.J. Shaefer Associates, Washington, a closely held defense technical assessment concern, for as much as $36.3 million in cash and stock.    ERC, Fairfax, Va., a technical services concern, said it will make an initial payment of $13.8 million in cash and ERC stock and make further payments of as much as $22.5 million based on Schaefer profits over a two-year period.    ERC signed a letter of intent in August to purchase Schaefer. ERC plans to merge with Schaefer following shareholder approval by both concerns. An ERC spokesman said he expects the transaction to be completed by early January.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, ERC closed at $15.25 a share, up 37.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>